title: Which K-pop groups have funny names? - Quora

response.answer_text: Not all of these are necessarily “funny” but I names I found a bit strange or odd for one reason or another. Also just a disclaimer, I’m only judging these based on their name and name only. I’m not questioning the group itself, the members, their talents, or anything. GWSN - it’s the abbreviation for Gongwon Sonyeo which translates to “Girls in the Park”. I don’t care much for names that are abbreviations, there’s just so many now that it just doesn’t stick out. But “Girls in the Park”? Just seems like a strange idea for a group name.(G)I-DLE I get what they’re going for but I still misspell This name half the time, depending on day, you’ll get “(G)I-DLE” or “G-IDLE” or “GIDLE” from me. Also, every person I’ve seen so far always miss pronounces the name the first time around.B1A4 its literally the members blood type. One member is type B and 4 are type ALipBubble ldk, it just sound weird to me, like a blister on my lip.Bob Girls literally the group’s concept was that all members had Bob style haircuts…LedApple I don’t even think the group really knew what their name meant because they changed it a few times. One of them was “shine brightly as LED whenever they perform” another was A tribute to Led Zeppelin and the apple was to represent their “fresh image”Wanna One I know it’s supposed to sound like “one oh one” like produce 101 but idk, I never liked the name (love the group omg) took awhile to grow.IZ*ONE again, like wanna one, I get what they’re going for. But seeing people who’ve never seen the show or heard about the group try and decifer what the name is, is hilarious. “I zee one” “I Zone” “One Zee Asterisk one?”Super M Idk, then name feels a bit understated for a group that’s supposed to be like “SM’s avengers team” plus who hasn’t misread it as “Sperm” at least once. Even Kai, who’s a member of the group wrote Sperm once.ATEEZ I thought it was a acronym but apparently it means A TEEnagers Z? Where teenagers from A-Z can be fans? This is one of those meanings I wish I didn’t know.HINAPIA Hi New Amazing Utopia? It’s too bad they could take the name Pristin with them because it’s one of my favorites.Mamamoo it’s a sound that babies make?Snuper it means higher than superTEEN TOP- The name seems normal until you learn that its an abbrevation of: Teenager Emoboy Emotion Next Generation Talent Object PraiseKiss&Cry Idk, I just associate Kiss and Cry as the spot figure skaters sit with their coach as their scores are announced.BONUSBaby the name just sounds like there’s extra babies?HashTag this may just be a personal pet peeve, I just can’t think of a good meaning or reasoning behind a name like that. Like it makes it sound dated to this era of time and marketing wise, I don’t think it’s a smart move because It’s going to be hard to search up stuff. How are you going to look them up? #Hashtag? Hashtag Kpop group?B.S (formerly Rania) personally, I think this name is perfect for a group managed by DR Music, seeing how poorly they’ve managed/Promoted Rania over the years. Somehow they think changing the group name will change things, a load of BS if you ask me. Again nothing against the group, the company is terrible and should just let all the girls go.Cravity this name took me a bit, I kept reading it as “cavity” like the hole in your teeth.*btw I answered a similar question in the past so I did copy/paste some of my explanations, just thought I’d put that out there.

As I’ve delved into the Kpop omniverse, there have been many times when I’ll hear the name of a group and go, “What in the world were they thinking??”  [This is Cravity. These boys deserve a better name.] I know that this is Korean pop so they do not owe us names that make sense in English, but still. Do these names actually sound cool to Koreans? I can understand these “funny” names happening in 1st and 2nd gen but these days? C’mon. But maybe that’s part of Kpop’s charm, I dunno. If any of the agencies wants to run their names by me first, I’d be happy to help. No charge. My list (most already mentioned by others; this is about the name only, has nothing to do with them or their music): Cravity - looking at that name, I feel so relieved that my boys, Monsta X, got off easy. Why, Starship, why??(G)i-DLE: Did I even spell that right? Still don’t know how to pronounce that one. “G” ”eye” “dull”, would be my guess. Is their company trying to make their name like a secret handshake that only insiders know?IZ*ONE: Still don’t know how to pronounce that one either. “I” “Z” “won”? What’s with the asterisk?Wanna One: Wondered for the longest time why they were called that but partway through the season, it struck me like a thunderbolt lol.ATEEZ: Their name is actually ok considering that it was going to be KQ Fellaz (uggg…). They dodged a bullet on that one.SHINee: When I think of “shiny”, I think of sweaty people. No offense to the group itself.Super Junior: Just seems juvenile, like the title of a Saturday morning cartoon. No offense to the group itself.Mamamoo: Yeah, the cow imagery just doesn’t work for me. No offense to the group itself.MomolandWeki MekiFin.K.LSechskiesRoo’raN.FlyingGugudan: just looked up, it means “multiplication table” in Korean. Well, that didn’t help.Note 1: Don’t even get me started on the fandom names! Really, Wonho, “WENEE”’s?? Note 2: Makes me wonder if there are any Kpop groups’ names that I think are actually cool. Off the top of my head, I’d say EXO, Stray Kids, Blackpink, iKon. Note 3: Omg I just realized that 2NE1 was pronounced like “twenty-one”! I actually like that.

Not necessarily funny, but also odd: SuperM I never saw it, but my friends were all laughing about how the name sounds and looks like “sperm”. I guess the humour around the name was reinforced after Kai mistakenly wrote “sperm” as well.  2.HINAPIA Made up former Pristin members, HINAPIA, the name stood for “Hi New Amazing Utopia”. I honestly thought it was a name for a spice or something.  3. MAMAMOO I absolutely adore MAMAMOO, but when I first read their name, I immediately thought of a female cow. Who on earth thought it was a good idea to put “mama” and “moo” in a group name?  4. Weki Meki I originally thought the name was slightly strange, but then I discovered that it’s pronounced “wicky micky”. It sounds like the title of a children's song.  5. SNUPER Snooping? Trooper? Is this a detective group? Nope, its the name of a group made by Widmay Ent. Apparently it’s supposed to mean“Higher than Super”, but that raises even more questions. What is super? Super rapping? Super singing? I honestly don’t know.

If you’re going to ask me, I feel like every kpop group has funny names, if it’s not numbers it’s going to be colors, food, or random made up words. Red Velvet - it’s not that funny but whenever I hear Red Velvet they remind me of Red Velvet cake with cream cheese frosting, makes me hungry too lol.Fishingirls - their name is either they’re going to be fishing for girls or the girls’ job is to fish (nothing wrong with being a fisher but sounds a little funny to be a band name)GWSN - the abbreviation is fine, but 공원소녀 literally means “Girls in the Park”, why?Fanatics - the name is fine, but it sounds more like a fandom name than a group name(G)I-DLE - their group name is mentioned a lot, but (여자)아이들 literally means “female children” (maybe it means young girls but nah their name sounds funny)Bonusbaby - sounds like your christmas bonus is a baby lolEpisode (Formerly known as Vitamin Angel) - their former name sounds like your mom reminding you to drink your vitaminsf(x) - their name is straight up math, why SM?GeeGu - I don’t know what their name actually means but GeeGu sounds like baby language

Which K-pop groups have funny names? I'm just gonna run down Wikimedia's list of groups alphabetically and see what happens. Bulldog Mansion: Hiatus since 2004. Might be a good thing. Annyeongbada: “Bye Bye Sea” is their name. Cocosori: This could've easily been “cocoa sound" but no. They disbanded because they couldn't get along. Or they hated their name. Cross Gene: Debuted in 2012 and are still active? Fiestar: Smh. Fin.K.L.: “Their name stands for Fin Killing Liberty, and was intended to mean that the group stood against "the oppression of all freedom" (fin means "end" in Spanish and French).” That's a real stretch. Fanxy Red: Peviously known as FFC-Acrush or simply Acrush, nobody ever wanted to give this Chinese girl group a good name. 5tion: “is a South Korean boy band popular during the early 2000s. The group's name is pronounced ocean as a play on words with the Korean word for '5' being 'oh'.” Too much of a stretch. Berry Good: Sorry, but I'll always make fun of this. GWSN: Holy shit, read this…”GWSN is an abbreviation of Gongwon Sonyeo, "Gongwon": (lit. Park) which the group describes like a place "where anyone, who is male or female or old or young, can go and enjoy themselves, heal their wounds and dream". Well…okay, but… “The abbreviation also has a separate meaning in English, with G standing for 'Ground' and WSN standing for the directional markers 'West', 'South' and 'North', the significance being that the group wants to reach out to people from every direction.” It's still going… “'Gong-won' can also be translated into Gong, meaning Zero in Korean, and Won which represents the English word one; meaning that when the seven members get together, they will forever be one.” BRUH JUST PICK A THING!!! Honey Popcorn: Unknown for their non-hit “Bibidi Babidi Boo.” Or, better known as “Libbity bibbity" by that dude from the Liberty Mutual commercial. Nasty Nasty: Damn, they can't even be “pretty and nasty,” they just extra nasty period. “Nasty Nasty was a unit composed of ZE:A's Kevin, Nine Muses's Gyeongree and Sojin. It was formed by Star Empire Entertainment in 2014.” OnlyOneOf: “Is a South Korean boy group formed by RSVP and 8D Creative in 2019. The group debuted on May 28, 2019, with Dot Point Jump,” proving that RSVP can't name a song any better than they can name a group. PURPLEBECK: “combines the meaning of grandeur from “purple” and stream from “beck.” As streams join to create a river that leads to the sea, the group name holds the hope for their small start to lead to great results.” - aminoapps. Come on K-pop, now you're just fucking around. I can do this all day. Piggy Dolls, We Girls, Roo'ra, Snuper. Why? I want to know why. NOBODY LEAVES until I get answers as to why these names are all so silly! Just kidding, ya’ll can go. I'm out too.  (Pink Fantasy Seea, looking like she's glad to not be with Piggy Dolls anymore.) Okay bye.

“Crayon Pop" - No words. Although they had some bops.“Momoland” - This is definitely a cute name, but 'Momo' means idiot/asshole ..“N.Flying” - I always wondered what the N means .. what does it represent? What do you think?“Pristin" - It reminds me of “Kristen”. For some reason, I also think of diamonds .. LOL“X1” - Possibly one of the most confusing names I've ever heard ..“2000 Won" - I-“Big Mama" - Was this supposed to imply an insult or--“Nasty Nasty" - This feels like they insulted the group ..“Day6” - What about the other day? The 7th day left out might have been Monday ..“Papaya" - Fruits are the new norm? Pristin ^ (I don't hate these groups btw. I just think their names are strange/odd/funny. This is purely my opinion.) Bye.

I can't believe nobody here talked about Kitten Girls. Is it just me or does it sound a bit sexual? GreatGuys I mean they are great, they really are, but I'm not sure about this name… 2NE1 I actually really like this name, but how do you pronounce it? Twentyone? Two n e one? Twoniwon? I don't know. DrugRestaurant Aren't drugs illegal in south korea hmhm? Lol Stray Kids I'm don't know… why do they stray? Just for you to make them stay? I don't get it lmao. f(x) I- sorry, I just don't like maths… B2ast/Beast I love this name, but “Boys 2 Search for Top” and “Boys of East Asia Standing Tall”… But my favorit is still: DickPunks Wait what?😳 Also groupnames I always laugh a bit about are the ones that are german words, for example Guckkasten (I don't even know what this means (something like watchbox?), but it's hillarious) or HerzAnalog (this is kinda beautiful tho (Herz = Heart)). Thanks for reading ^^
There is this rookie girlgroup that recently debuted and their group name is Craxy. I guess it stands for crazy and sexy?? idk but it sounds off to me
